# =============================================================================
# ide006_cold_kv_long_ctx.env — IDE_006 scenario (long-context + Offloading
# Connector). The active toggle is the vLLM built-in OffloadingConnector
# (cold-tier KV offload). IDE_006 second-cut item (a) is enabled; (b) the
# CPU partial-attention path stays OFF (use ide006_cold_kv_split_on_long_ctx
# .env to flip that on).
#
# What this scenario therefore validates (orthogonal to the split-on env):
#   1. Whether cold KV actually moves to CPU DRAM (server.log +
#      monitor_cpu.csv).
#   2. Whether the output is semantically consistent with the
#      vllm_original_long_ctx.env baseline (`vllm bench serve` does not dump
#      token ids — indirect verification).
#   3. OffloadingConnector long-context stability on its own (no crashes).
#
# Scenario:
#   - INPUT_LEN=14336   (max_model_len 16384 - output 128 - margin 1920)
#   - OUTPUT_LEN=128
#   - NUM_PROMPTS=100   (sized to overflow prod GPU KV pool — see
#                       vllm_original_long_ctx.env header for sizing rationale)
#   - MAX_MODEL_LEN=16384
#   - GPU_MEMORY_UTIL=0.85 (margin for OffloadingConnector CPU buffer)
#   - cpu_bytes_to_use=512 GiB (vllm/v1/kv_offload/cpu/spec.py:32-35 사이징
#                               공식: num_cpu_blocks = cpu_bytes_to_use //
#                               (per-block-bytes × world_size). Llama-70B +
#                               TP=8 에서 한 블록 (16 tokens) 의 전 TP rank
#                               합산 KV 가 ~5.24 MB 이므로, 100 × 14336 =
#                               1,433,600 tokens 수용에 필요한 양은 437 GiB.
#                               안전 마진 포함 512 GiB → 89,478 blocks 위에
#                               1,433,600 tokens 의 ~17 % headroom 으로
#                               'cannot store N blocks' 경고 완전 제거.
#                               가용 RAM 1.9 TiB 의 27 %, NUMA 한쪽 node
#                               (~950 GB) 의 54 % 까지 → first-touch 가 한쪽
#                               socket 에 몰려도 OOM 위험 없음. NUMA 인지
#                               자체는 TSK_004 가 throughput sweep 진입 전에
#                               처리. 정확도 (TST_003) 에는 NUMA 무관.)
#
# Comparison pair: vllm_original_long_ctx.env (same sweep, OffloadingConnector
# off).
# Hardware reference: prod box (Xeon Sapphire Rapids+ + H100 x 8).
# Model: meta-llama/Llama-3.3-70B-Instruct, TP=8.
# See: shadow_assists/features/IDE_006/README.md
# =============================================================================

# --- Model ---
MODEL=meta-llama/Llama-3.3-70B-Instruct
PORT=8000
HOST=127.0.0.1

# --- Server ---
GPU_MEMORY_UTIL=0.85
TENSOR_PARALLEL_SIZE=8
MAX_MODEL_LEN=16384

# IDE_006 (a) — cold-tier KV offload via OffloadingConnector.
# cpu_bytes_to_use=16 GiB sized for Llama-3.3-70B + TP=8: per-rank GPU KV
# blocks come and go through this CPU mirror, well within the prod box's
# system RAM. block_size key is intentionally omitted so block_size_factor
# defaults to 1 (matches the only configuration TSK_002 currently supports
# on the cold path; harmless for the connector-only scenario as well).
EXTRA_SERVE_ARGS='--kv-transfer-config={"kv_connector":"OffloadingConnector","kv_role":"kv_both","kv_connector_extra_config":{"cpu_bytes_to_use":549755813888}}'

# --- Benchmark ---
BACKEND=vllm
DATASET_NAME=random
NUM_PROMPTS=100
INPUT_LEN=1024
OUTPUT_LEN=14336
REQUEST_RATE=inf

# --- Monitoring ---
MONITOR_INTERVAL=1

# --- Results ---
RESULTS_DIR=results

# --- Server readiness ---
SERVER_READY_TIMEOUT=900
SERVER_READY_POLL=5
